legacy.name: Akshay Saini

result.text:
Have you ever used Search Bar on Amazon or Youtube?
They don't wait for you to hit the `Search` button
It would be a Bad UX 🤷🏽‍♂️
Instead, as you start typing, it shows Suggestions ✅
Suggestions are fetched via network calls, and
Network Calls are Expensive 😰
So,
How do they optimize performance along with a Good UX?

let me explain,
They use the concept of, `Debouncing` ✅

Debouncing limits the rate at which a function is invoked. This practice improves browser performance as well as maintain a good UX. 🚀

Not just for Search Bar, it is widely used across the application to optimize performance.

That's why `Debouncing` is a HOT Interview Question. 🔥

In Namaste React web series,
we build a project "Namaste Youtube" (kind of a YT clone in React)
there I cover `Debouncing` in detail using React to build Search Bar.

If you're interested, checkout  `Namaste React`- https://t.co/fb0V8NyYfd 

Cheers,
Akshay Saini
#amazon #flipkart #javascript #softwareengineer
